tp:treatment-sec.p:
Description ( Figs 11 a–c). Encrusting, consolidating dead coral rubble. The type was described as creeping with disc-like attachment. Our specimens are similarly patchy, but may also be somewhat thicker forming cushions. Oscules are usually slightly raised above the surface. Sizes usually do not exceed several cm 2 . Surface smooth but irregular. Consistency soft. Color where recorded red or blood-red (cf. photo in
Lim et al . 2008
).
